<span id="freeTextContainer1057159772793206288">I really enjoy this kind of fairy tale re-told genre. This one intrigued me from the start and I spent the evening reading it instead of folding laundry. There was a lot more action in this version of the Little Mermaid, which was exciting, but I have to admit I think Pearl ended up with the wrong guy at the end! I loved Pearl and her friendship with Prince James. That is exactly the kind of friendship that grows into true love and I was waiting for that to happen, when all of a sudden another l</span>
  <span id="freeText1057159772793206288" style="display:none">I really enjoy this kind of fairy tale re-told genre. This one intrigued me from the start and I spent the evening reading it instead of folding laundry. There was a lot more action in this version of the Little Mermaid, which was exciting, but I have to admit I think Pearl ended up with the wrong guy at the end! I loved Pearl and her friendship with Prince James. That is exactly the kind of friendship that grows into true love and I was waiting for that to happen, when all of a sudden another love interest shows up from nowhere. I don't necessarily mind the twist, it's just that we never go to know Kale as much as we did James and Pearls love for him seemed to be based on nothing much at all. Still, it was a fun, easy read and great escape for a day!</span>
