        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2321819605" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13368503735235736152">This was a pretty disappointing read for me. <br/><br/>I managed to get through it because it was short, I enjoyed the twists on the original fairy tale, and I wanted to know what happened to Pearl. <br/><br/>The beginning hooked me in and really made me want to know more. Unfortunately it went downhill from there. The pacing felt very off to me; the set up took way too long, we had new and very key characters introduced halfway through the book, and the ending was rushed and anticlimactic. In addition, there was a</span>
  <span id="freeText13368503735235736152" style="display:none">This was a pretty disappointing read for me. <br /><br />I managed to get through it because it was short, I enjoyed the twists on the original fairy tale, and I wanted to know what happened to Pearl. <br /><br />The beginning hooked me in and really made me want to know more. Unfortunately it went downhill from there. The pacing felt very off to me; the set up took way too long, we had new and very key characters introduced halfway through the book, and the ending was rushed and anticlimactic. In addition, there was a lot of instalove and convenient play points, the political enemies and schemes fizzled out, the ending was predictable, and the dialogue felt very awkward (it was often used to get across information about the plot, didn't feel unique to the characters, and felt choppy in many places). <br /><br />Overall, I wouldn't recommend this.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13368503735235736152" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


