<div id="review_143209909" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/143209909" />
    <a title="Melissa A DeJesus" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/136894-melissa-a-dejesus"><img alt="Melissa A DeJesus" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1611780871p2/136894.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/143209909?book_show_action=true">Jan 24, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Melissa A DeJesus" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Melissa A DeJesus" href="/user/show/136894-melissa-a-dejesus">Melissa A DeJesus</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Mass Market Paperback " href="/book/show/7687402-midnight-pearls">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/136894-melissa-a-dejesus?shelf=kid-books">kid-books</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/136894-melissa-a-dejesus?shelf=retellings">retellings</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer143209909" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2492231976733918167">If you like Hans Christian Andersen&apos;s or Disney&apos;s Little Mermaid, you&apos;ll love this retelling by Debbie Viguie. Part of a collection entitled &quot;Once Upon a Time,&quot; this story takes a twist on a classic. This time the little mermaid is actually human. Cursed by the sea witch to live on land, Pearl is unaware of her origin or history. She was found as a baby by the local fisherman, but has known since then that she is different from everyone else. She befriends the prince and soon friendship turns in</span>
  <span id="freeText2492231976733918167" style="display:none">If you like Hans Christian Andersen's or Disney's Little Mermaid, you'll love this retelling by Debbie Viguie. Part of a collection entitled "Once Upon a Time," this story takes a twist on a classic. This time the little mermaid is actually human. Cursed by the sea witch to live on land, Pearl is unaware of her origin or history. She was found as a baby by the local fisherman, but has known since then that she is different from everyone else. She befriends the prince and soon friendship turns into more as the prince must choose a bride. But when he takes Pearl on a boat ride to propose, a storm arises and he is rescued by a mermaid name Faye. She is the sister of Kale, a merman who has loved Pearl since they were children and has been searching for her ever since her disappearance. Reader will find classic elements from both versions of the Little Mermaid tale and will love them just the same.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2492231976733918167" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


